        "heading": "Clinical Note",
        "section_value": "Chief Complaint\nReports left back pain, primarily on the left side, which prompted a visit to evaluate the symptoms.\nHistory of Present Illness\nThe patient reports experiencing back pain, primarily on the left side, for several days. The pain is described as varying in intensity, sometimes sharp, sometimes not, and occasionally moves. It is often present but not always. He reports that the pain is not consistently present and sometimes moves. He has not noticed any changes in his appetite or water consumption, though he has been drinking more water recently and experiencing increased nighttime urination. He denies recent trauma. The patient reports that school is going well and that his grades are good. He has not noticed any illness among his classmates or siblings. He reports a history of recurrent strep infections, having experienced four in the last five months, as diagnosed by his previous physician. He states that he follows his doctor's instructions regarding treatment for these infections.\nFindings\nPhysical examination reveals no tenderness to palpation of the back, no rebound tenderness, and no guarding. Lung sounds are clear to auscultation bilaterally. Heart sounds are normal, with no murmurs or rubs. Neurological examination is unremarkable. Vital signs are within normal limits.\nAssessment",
